<br>
Our pull tactics evolve with the situation on pulling, which is step one of AE.<br>
<br>
If it's a large pull and we just want it all now, we will send a paladin or cleric invulned to pull, sometimes we follow them to a distination we select as our AE spot ahead of time.  When we do the follow method, we give them a 5-10 second head start.  Other times we'll pull about 3-4 mobs and have our enchanter mez them all, then pull another wave of 4+ mobs and start to AE.  You want to be able to get all your mobs to you without a dead puller, or near dead puller, or your cleric is healing them just as your casters are going to potentially get beat on bad, and that time can cause a spiral death sequence.  Pulling is important.<br>
<br>
If we pull in phases and have a shaman, which we frequently do, she'll cast turgurs on them to limit the damage they can do once the battle starts.  Our enchanter will usually cast AE tash on them at this point as well, to make AE stuns more effective.<br>
<br>
Now we have a bunch of mobs infront of you, at this point, our enchanter usually throws down an AE tash to lead off, at which point I try to land my AE nuke (scintilation) at the same time, so I get beat on, and not her.  She follows up with AE stuns.  She has 3-4 AE stuns mem'ed and cycles through them as we AE nuke (usually just me and a wizard/druid).  As all this is going on, the cleric uses remedy, our shaman uses greater or superior heal, and if we are lucky, so is our paladin.<br>
<br>
Once everything is down to 1 or 2 mobs (the biggest, usually high level mobs), we frequently stop the AE nukes, and just finish off them with melee.  Sometimes we run out of mana before it's over, at which point, our enchanter will mez them (which we have to make sure she knows when we do), and we finish them off with a pet and melee.  Sometimes, I'll call of our cleric to AE with us, if I know we don't have enough mana to even come close to finishing them.  If 4 mobs are still standing after you are OOM, he's healing mana is futile, but if he AE's with you, you just might kill them all.<br>
<br>
Now you have killed a huge pull, frequently, you are in a room that will spawn 3+ mobs.  This is bad, if all the mobs are killed at once, every mob will spawn at once.  So you can't stand in a room you AE'ed down.  What we do to avoid respawn is to move after each AE battle to where we pulled the mobs from.  (exception is when we all move to where the mobs are to do AE.)  In any case, keep moving if you AE.<br>
<br>
Best part about AE is all the people going <br>
OMG <br>
FOOK! <br>
YOU ARE ALL GOING TO DIE!<br>
and the wizard from an on looking group going, &quot;I want to do that!&quot;<br>
&lt;someone&gt; tells you, 'tell me when you put your next AE group together'<br>
<br>
The unfortunately truth is you will die once in a while.  Things happen fast, and if the whole group isn't paying attention, people die.  It's very important to constantly keep everyone updated on what exactly the plan is.<br>
<br>
P.S. - forgot to mention, as a nuker, you want to be taking the damage.  Your enchanter depends on other people getting hit so that the resisted mobs don't prevent her from stunning again.  This is why point blanks are so crutial.  Don't let a wizard tell you his pillar spells are better for AE, not for this they aren't. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzantenvaliturus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zanten Valiturus</A> at: 1/25/01 6:51:22 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=waldenawildfyre>Waldena Wildfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#333333>(1/26/01 2:08:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 12,000 damages in one nuke ?</span><hr size=1> Someone said that the PBAEs dont have a limit, but it depends on the spells.  The pre50 PBAE have a 3 thing limit like the rains (I tested it when clearing out crap when I was camping AC in SRO a while ago).  As for scintilation ive heard it has a limit around 14 or 15 also, but it might be unlimited, hard to get enough guys in one spot to test it out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uteramenor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teramenor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#333333>(1/26/01 8:32:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topi